h5. Create a Grails project
* using command line or you favoutrite IDE
{code}
grails create-app bookstore
cd bookstore
{code}

Our plugin is not yet publish in grails repository, in the meantime

* fork or clone projects from github.com/3musket33rs/htm5-mobile-scaffolding

* Add dependencies to BuildConfig.groovy file
- jsonp plugin for cross domain applicaion. If you want to package your application as an hybrid applciation, this dependency is required.
- html5-mobile-scoffolding

h4. Create a domain class
{code}
grails create-domain-class bookstore.Book
{code}

* add content to it
{code}
class Book {
    String name
    String isbn
    Double latitude
    Double longitude
    static constraints = {}
}
{code}
h4. Generate JSON Controller and HTML view

You can generate both in one go:
{code}
grails create-domain-class bookstore.Book
{code}

When geolocalisation is activated, book list can be rendered as map (default render) 
!book-as-map-geolocation.png!

You can switch to list rendering:
!book-as-list-geolocation.png!